line_2: In Notes more sweet he doth his Sorrows tell,
Whose musick could alone your warbling notes excel.

line_1: The solemn dirge be sung by Philomel;
line_2: The fateful raven tolls the passing bell,

line_1: Sound not one Note unless sad Philomel.
line_2: The less gay verdant Look ye Birds be still,

line_1: O fail not then, sweet Philomel,
